Full Description: In the brief period since M3's inception in 2007, we have aligned with over 75 independent brokerage agencies and broker-dealers, with the single goal of helping grow their fixed business. We look forward to earning the right to count you among our strategic partners, and guarantee a release to you and your down line should you ever decide to pursue another relationship. However, we're confident that this is a promise we'll never have to deliver on. Like any marketplace, the insurance and annuity arena is always changing. In recent years, the fixed annuity space has grown to a $98 billion industry, with fixed-indexed products accounting for over $54 billion of that figure. Current trends indicate that those numbers only stand to get larger in the years to come, with fixed-indexed annuities comprising an ever-increasing piece of the pie. Our aim at M3 is to rapidly grow this portion of your business by giving your producers the resources they need to effectively position fixed annuities, and the guarantees they offer, within your clients' portfolios. Even as fixed annuities grow in popularity, there is still plenty of information out there that is either outdated or simply inaccurate. A partnership with us gives you access to a staff well-versed in the ins and outs of fixed products, and the situations for which they are most appropriate. We understand that fixed annuities aren't necessarily for every client, or for a client's whole portfolio. Even so, with access to over 30 carriers, we can bring additional value to any book of business.

Falcon Isle Resources has identified a major high quality phosphate resource in the Diamond Creek Phosphate Operations.
Headquarters Regions: Greater Los Angeles Area, West Coast, Western US
Full Description: As part of their commitment to help ensure global and US food security, Falcon Isle Resources has identified a major high quality phosphate resource in the Diamond Creek Phosphate Operations. This rich deposit on 840 acres will contribute essential mineral elements to the downstream production of high demand fertilizers such as DAP, MAP and Superphosphate, products necessary to meet rising agricultural demand. Their high-grade phosphate ore has been tested and identified as a major source of organic direct application fertilizer to help meet the growing demand for organic foods in the US.    To date, initial sample testing has confirmed Diamond Creek’s high grade phosphate ore averaging over 28% P205 with estimated surface and underground resources of over 15,000,000 tons. Continued exploration activity and a pre-feasibility study will be conducted to establish probable resource quantities, qualities and location. These studies will be the basis to determine mine plan design and extraction activity moving forward.    Initial Plan of Operations have outlined Phase I strip mining to extract approximately 3,880,000 tons of high grade phosphate ore, averaging over 28% P205. The Diamond Creek Phosphate Mine is strategically located in mining friendly Utah and near multiple major downstream processing and fertilizer manufacturing facilities.
Industry Groups: Food and Beverage, Health Care, Manufacturing, Sustainability
